<p>How can we implement this feature in Polymer?</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/CMsNt.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/CMsNt.png" alt="confirmation example"></a></p>  <p>(example from github wiki page editing)</p>  <p>I suppose we have an application based on the <a href="https://developers.google.com/web/tools/polymer-starter-kit/index?hl=en" rel="nofollow">Polymer Starter Kit</a> (so with <a href="https://visionmedia.github.io/page.js/" rel="nofollow">page.js</a> as router engine)</p>  <ul> <li>my application uses a <code>product-editor</code> element which contains a textarea + a save button. </li> <li>User is editing a product at the route <code>localhost/#!/product/127/edit</code></li> <li>He "accidentally" clicks on the Back button or other links on the page</li> </ul>  <p>I'd like to display the above confirmation dialog: <code>"Are you sure to leave..."</code></p>  <p>How can we do this?</p>